</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex>f \colon  A \to  B</fr:tex> be <fr:link
href="erct-000U.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000U">biinvertible</fr:link> with <fr:tex>s,r \colon  B \to  A</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>h_s \colon  f  \circ  s  \sim   1_{ B }</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>h_r \colon  r \circ  f =  1_{ A }</fr:tex>. Then we may define a homotopy <fr:tex>h'  \colon  s \circ  f  \sim   1_{ A }</fr:tex> exhibiting <fr:tex>s \colon  B \to  A</fr:tex> as a retraction of <fr:tex>f \colon  A \to  B</fr:tex>. Therefore, we may define a <fr:link
href="erct-000X.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000X">quasi-inverse</fr:link> to <fr:tex>f</fr:tex> tracked by <fr:tex>s \colon  B \to  A</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
